doc.previous: The airline was established in 1995 and started operations on 31 August 1995. It began operation of Lockheed L-382 Hercules aircraft in 1997. It has 140 employees.[2] The company has a Civil Reserve Air Fleet contract with the United States Department of Defense.[citation needed]
doc.after: Lynden Air Cargo operates the following domestic scheduled freight services:[2] Anchorage, Bethel, Kotzebue and Nome.
